channel.title: Help with compile
channel.description:
Ok, i try to add a new case then go to the compiler. it comes up with this:
[code]
client.java:15292: orphaned case case 252:
client.java:17579: illegal start of expression public String passHash(String password) {
2 errors[/code]
So, i think that it must have been me adding the new case that caused the error. I delete the new case...
But then the same error! It was working before i added case, and now i dunno what to do. It doesnt make much sense, because i have not edited what it is talking about in the compiler.. Help please!
